<h2>What this partner does</h2>
<p>Bring an IPCC AR6 figure (temperature anomaly time series, SSP scenario projection, regional climate-impact map) and the Climate Modeler helps you decode it. What does this projection say? What does it NOT say? What's the confidence-level language doing? What model assumptions sit underneath the number? Particularly useful when you're translating from global-average claims to Chennai-specific implications for your <a href="/units/unit-4/assessment-chennai-climate-brief/">Climate Brief</a>.</p>

<h2>What this partner won't do</h2>
<p>It won't write your Brief. It won't make confident claims about specific Chennai events (a particular cyclone track, a specific monsoon-onset date). It won't pretend climate models have more precision than they actually have — and it's honest about model limitations (parametrisation choices, grid resolution, what's not included). Projection vs. prediction is a distinction it'll hold the line on. The "one thing the AI got wrong" gate applies — expect to disagree with it at least once per session.</p>

<h2>Documentation reminder</h2>
<p>Every substantive Climate Modeler conversation that feeds into your Climate Brief gets logged in the <a href="/foundations/ai-documentation-protocol/">AI Documentation Template</a>. Same rules as the last three units.</p>

